\begin{frame}{Empirical Study Schedule}
   \begin{itemize}
       \item The following steps should be followed
       \begin{itemize}
           \item Finalization of research question and construction of testable hypothesis
           \item Extensive literature review on the topic esp. on DCE applications
           \item Study scope, area, sample etc.
           \item Sampling strategy 
           \item Construction of questionnaire
           \item Development of DCE
           \item Field Phase (pretesting and survey conduction)
           \item Data Preparation and Analysis
           \item Writing a scientific paper
           
       \end{itemize}
   \end{itemize} 
\end{frame}

\begin{frame}{Empirical Study}
\begin{itemize}
    \item The product of the empirical study should a scientific paper, which we submit to an international peer reviewed journal.
    \item The whole group gets one grade for the paper.
    \item Submission to a journal is voluntary, and costs a lot of additional work, but will be honored with authorship.
    \item From the beginning of the study, keep in mind that the work is academically, and should compile to all academic standards. 
    \item Practical relevance is important but the aim is to gather scientifically sound knowledge. We will not solve problems, but provide implications for practitioners. 
\end{itemize}
    
\end{frame}

